paragraph.value: Table 2 shows a selection of the f1-scores achieved on properties in the CSLB dataset in relation to the
cosine similarity of the associated words. A
average cosine similarity means that the concepts overall have similar vector representations and can thus be seen as having a
diversity. The results of the Spearman Rank correlation clearly indicate that scores achieved by nearest neighbors correlate more strongly with the
cosine than the two supervised classification approaches.
